ifLoopbackTestTable.name: ifLoopbackTestTable
ifLoopbackTestTable.description: This table contains input and results of a packet loopback test. This table is indexed by ifIndex. This is a interface related test. There can be only one test running per interface. This table should be used in conjunction with ifTestTable(Rfc 1573) with all the semantics of ifTestTable.

ifLoopbackTestEntry.name: ifLoopbackTestEntry
ifLoopbackTestEntry.description: An entry containing objects for test input and result for packet loopback test

loopbackTestInputNumCycles.name: loopbackTestInputNumCycles
loopbackTestInputNumCycles.description: This object corresponds the number of cycles the test to be run for. One cycle corresponds to a 15 second interval. The default value for this object is 40.

loopbackTestResultsPktsSent.name: loopbackTestResultsPktsSent
loopbackTestResultsPktsSent.description: This object corresponds to the number of packets sent

loopbackTestResultsPktsRcvdOK.name: loopbackTestResultsPktsRcvdOK
loopbackTestResultsPktsRcvdOK.description: This object corresponds to the number of packets which were received without any error

loopbackTestResultsPktsRcvdErr.name: loopbackTestResultsPktsRcvdErr
loopbackTestResultsPktsRcvdErr.description: This object corresponds to the number of packets which were received with errors

loopbackTestResultsPktsNotRcvd.name: loopbackTestResultsPktsNotRcvd
loopbackTestResultsPktsNotRcvd.description: This object corresponds to the number of packets which were sent but not received

loopbackTestResultsPktErrorRate.name: loopbackTestResultsPktErrorRate
loopbackTestResultsPktErrorRate.description: Reflects the error rate of the loopback test. this string will represent a floating point number of the form [ErrRate][eE][+-][ErrRateBase] where ErrRate and ErrRateBase are integers. In Other Words ErrRate * [10^ -ErrRateBase] shown below are example of the values returned. 123456E-5 = 1.23456 344567e-6 = 0.344567

loopbackTestResultsErrSecs.name: loopbackTestResultsErrSecs
loopbackTestResultsErrSecs.description: This object corresponds to the number of errored seconds

loopbackTestResultsSvrErrSecs.name: loopbackTestResultsSvrErrSecs
loopbackTestResultsSvrErrSecs.description: This object corresponds to the number of severely errored seconds

loopbackTestResultsElpTime.name: loopbackTestResultsElpTime
loopbackTestResultsElpTime.description: This object corresponds to the number of seconds elapsed since the start of the test.

ifBERTObjectsTable.name: ifBERTObjectsTable
ifBERTObjectsTable.description: This table contains the objects for Bit Error Rate Test. This table is indexed by ifIndex.

ifBERTObjectsEntry.name: ifBERTObjectsEntry
ifBERTObjectsEntry.description: An Entry containing objects of BERT.

ifBERTTestDuration.name: ifBERTTestDuration
ifBERTTestDuration.description: This object represents the test duration in seconds.

ifBERTElapsedTime.name: ifBERTElapsedTime
ifBERTElapsedTime.description: This object represents the elapsed time in seconds.

ifBERTDownSyncUP.name: ifBERTDownSyncUP
ifBERTDownSyncUP.description: This object indicates whether Downstream sync is enabled .

ifBERTUpSyncUP.name: ifBERTUpSyncUP
ifBERTUpSyncUP.description: This object indicates whether upstream sync is enabled.

ifBERTSegmentsSent.name: ifBERTSegmentsSent
ifBERTSegmentsSent.description: This object represents the number of segments sent during the test

ifBERTDownMBitsRcvd.name: ifBERTDownMBitsRcvd
ifBERTDownMBitsRcvd.description: This represents the number of million bits rcvd downstream.

ifBERTUpMBitsRcvd.name: ifBERTUpMBitsRcvd
ifBERTUpMBitsRcvd.description: This represents the number of million bits rcvd upstream.

ifBERTDownBitErrDetected.name: ifBERTDownBitErrDetected
ifBERTDownBitErrDetected.description: This represents the number of bit errors detected downstream.

ifBERTUpBitErrDetected.name: ifBERTUpBitErrDetected
ifBERTUpBitErrDetected.description: This represents the number of bit errors detected upstream.

ifBERTDownBitErrRate.name: ifBERTDownBitErrRate
ifBERTDownBitErrRate.description: This string will represent a floating point number of the form [Er rRate] [eE] [+-] [ErrRatebase] where ErrTare and errRateBase are integers.

ifBERTUpBitErrRate.name: ifBERTUpBitErrRate
ifBERTUpBitErrRate.description: This object reflects the error rate of BERT in Upstream direction. This string will represent a floating point number of the form [ErrRate] [eE] [+-] [ErrRatebase] where ErrTare and errRateBase are integers.

ifBERTDownErroredSecs.name: ifBERTDownErroredSecs
ifBERTDownErroredSecs.description: This represents number of errored seconds downstream. Errored second is a second in which there is at least 1 block error.

ifBERTUpErroredSecs.name: ifBERTUpErroredSecs
ifBERTUpErroredSecs.description: This represents number of errored seconds upstream. Errored second is a second in which there is at least 1 block error.

ifBERTDownLineRate.name: ifBERTDownLineRate
ifBERTDownLineRate.description: This represents the downstream line rate in KBPS

ifBERTUpLineRate.name: ifBERTUpLineRate
ifBERTUpLineRate.description: This represents the Upstream line rate in KBPS

ifBERTDownMargin.name: ifBERTDownMargin
ifBERTDownMargin.description: This represents the Downstream margin in decibels (DB).

ifBERTUpMargin.name: ifBERTUpMargin
ifBERTUpMargin.description: This represents the upstream margin in decibels (DB).

ifBLERTObjectsTable.name: ifBLERTObjectsTable
ifBLERTObjectsTable.description: This table contains the objects for Block Error Rate Test (BLERT). This table is indexed by ifIndex.

ifBLERTObjectsEntry.name: ifBLERTObjectsEntry
ifBLERTObjectsEntry.description: An Entry containing objects of BLERT.

ifBLERTTestDuration.name: ifBLERTTestDuration
ifBLERTTestDuration.description: This object represents the test duration in seconds.

ifBLERTElapsedTime.name: ifBLERTElapsedTime
ifBLERTElapsedTime.description: This object represents the elapsed time in seconds since the test started.

ifBLERTTxSeqCount.name: ifBLERTTxSeqCount
ifBLERTTxSeqCount.description: This object indicates the next Tx sequence.

ifBLERTRxSeqCount.name: ifBLERTRxSeqCount
ifBLERTRxSeqCount.description: This object indicates the next Rx sequence.

ifBLERTRxGoodFrames.name: ifBLERTRxGoodFrames
ifBLERTRxGoodFrames.description: This object indicates the number of good frames received.

ifBLERTTxGoodFrames.name: ifBLERTTxGoodFrames
ifBLERTTxGoodFrames.description: This object indicates the number of good frames transmitted.

ifBLERTRxBadFrames.name: ifBLERTRxBadFrames
ifBLERTRxBadFrames.description: This object indicates the number of bad frames received.

ifBLERTTxBadFrames.name: ifBLERTTxBadFrames
ifBLERTTxBadFrames.description: This object indicates the number of bad frames transmitted.

ifBLERTDnLineRate.name: ifBLERTDnLineRate
ifBLERTDnLineRate.description: This object indicates the downstream line rate.

ifBLERTUpLineRate.name: ifBLERTUpLineRate
ifBLERTUpLineRate.description: This object indicates the upstream line rate.

applMaxNumberOfTests.name: applMaxNumberOfTests
applMaxNumberOfTests.description: This object identifies the maximum number of application based tests that can be simultaneously instantiated on the device.

applCurrentNumberOfTests.name: applCurrentNumberOfTests
applCurrentNumberOfTests.description: This object identifies the current number of application based tests that are running on the device.

applStopAllTests.name: applStopAllTests
applStopAllTests.description: The value of this object corresponds to stop all application based tests on the device. noOp -- no operation stop -- all the application tests will be stopped but current test results are still available stopAndClear -- all the application tests will be stoped and the results are cleared also

applNewTestId.name: applNewTestId
applNewTestId.description: This value of this object corresponds to getting a magic number to start an application based test. The magic number is used as an index to create a row for the diagApplTestTable. If no new rows can be created, this object will have a value of 0.

applTestStatusTable.name: applTestStatusTable
applTestStatusTable.description: This table controls all the application tests. It defines a test type, starts a test, and clears a test.

applTestStatusEntry.name: applTestStatusEntry
applTestStatusEntry.description: An entry containing objects for invoking application based tests

applTestId.name: applTestId
applTestId.description: A unique ID to identify each application test.

applTestType.name: applTestType
applTestType.description: This object defines the application test type.

applTestStatus.name: applTestStatus
applTestStatus.description: This object shows the current status of an application test. none - indicates waiting for test parameters. inProgress - indicates the test is in process. success - indicates the test is completed. failed - indicates the test is failed. abort - indicates the test was aborted

applTestErrorCode.name: applTestErrorCode
applTestErrorCode.description: This object shows the reason for a test failure.

applTestOwner.name: applTestOwner
applTestOwner.description: The network manager who has started the test

applTestRowStatus.name: applTestRowStatus
applTestRowStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or delete an existing row for an application test.

applPingTestTable.name: applPingTestTable
applPingTestTable.description: This table contains objects which allow network manager to ping a destination.

applPingTestEntry.name: applPingTestEntry
applPingTestEntry.description: This table contains the input parameters for a ping test and the results of the ping test.

applPingTestId.name: applPingTestId
applPingTestId.description: A unique ID to identify each application test.

applPingTestIpAddress.name: applPingTestIpAddress
applPingTestIpAddress.description: The IP address to be pinged.

applPingTestSourceIpAddr.name: applPingTestSourceIpAddr
applPingTestSourceIpAddr.description: The Source IP address where we are pinging from. This is an optional object for some devices. See operational specification for its use.

applPingTestPacketSize.name: applPingTestPacketSize
applPingTestPacketSize.description: This object corresponds to the size of the packet (in bytes) which will be sent during the Ping test. The default value for this object is 64 bytes

applPingTestTimeout.name: applPingTestTimeout
applPingTestTimeout.description: This object corresponds to a timeout value (in seconds) between Pings. The default value for this object is 5 seconds

applPingTestMaxPings.name: applPingTestMaxPings
applPingTestMaxPings.description: This object corresponds to the maximum number of times the device should Ping for the destination. The default value for this object is 10

applPingTestPktsSent.name: applPingTestPktsSent
applPingTestPktsSent.description: This object corresponds to the total number of packets sent.

applPingTestPktsRecv.name: applPingTestPktsRecv
applPingTestPktsRecv.description: This object corresponds to the total number of packets received without error

applPingTestDomain.name: applPingTestDomain
applPingTestDomain.description: This object specifies the destination ip address's domain. The Default is service domain. Not allowed if source ip address is entered. This is an optional object for some devices. See operational specification its use.

applPingTestIfIndex.name: applPingTestIfIndex
applPingTestIfIndex.description: This object specifies the interface over which the ping test will take place.

applTracerouteConfigTable.name: applTracerouteConfigTable
applTracerouteConfigTable.description: This table contains objects which allow network manager to enter the parameters of a traceroute test.

applTracerouteConfigEntry.name: applTracerouteConfigEntry
applTracerouteConfigEntry.description: This table contains the input parameters for a traceroute test.

applTracerouteTestId.name: applTracerouteTestId
applTracerouteTestId.description: A unique ID to identify each application test.

applTracerouteIpAddress.name: applTracerouteIpAddress
applTracerouteIpAddress.description: The destination IP address of a traceroute test.

applTracerouteSourceIpAddr.name: applTracerouteSourceIpAddr
applTracerouteSourceIpAddr.description: The source IP address of where the traceroute test started. This is an optional object for some devices. See operational specification for its use.

applTraceroutePktsSize.name: applTraceroutePktsSize
applTraceroutePktsSize.description: This object corresponds to the size of the packet (in bytes) which will be sent during the traceroute test. Please refer to product specific documentation for the default values supported

applTracerouteTimeout.name: applTracerouteTimeout
applTracerouteTimeout.description: This object corresponds to a timeout value (in seconds) of a traceroute test. The default value for this object is 5 seconds

applTracerouteMaxHops.name: applTracerouteMaxHops
applTracerouteMaxHops.description: This object corresponds to the maximum number of hops to reach the destination. The default value for this object is device specific. See Operational Specifications

applTracerouteDomain.name: applTracerouteDomain
applTracerouteDomain.description: This object specifies the destination ip address's domain. The Default is service domain. Not allowed if source ip address is entered. This is an optional object for some devices. See operational specification its use.

applTracerouteIfIndex.name: applTracerouteIfIndex
applTracerouteIfIndex.description: This object specifies the interface over which the trace-route test will take place.

applTracerouteResultTable.name: applTracerouteResultTable
applTracerouteResultTable.description: This table contains results of traceroute test.

applTracerouteResultEntry.name: applTracerouteResultEntry
applTracerouteResultEntry.description: An entry contains the objects for the traceroute test.

applTracerouteResultTestId.name: applTracerouteResultTestId
applTracerouteResultTestId.description: A unique ID to identify each application test.

applTracerouteHopCount.name: applTracerouteHopCount
applTracerouteHopCount.description: This object contains the number of hops to reach the gateway.

applTracerouteIpAddr.name: applTracerouteIpAddr
applTracerouteIpAddr.description: This object contains the IP address of the gateway.

applTraceroutePktSize.name: applTraceroutePktSize
applTraceroutePktSize.description: This object corresponds to the size of the packet (in bytes) which will be sent during the traceroute test. Please refer to product specific documentation for the default values supported

applTracerouteProbe1RTT.name: applTracerouteProbe1RTT
applTracerouteProbe1RTT.description: This object contains the round trip time (rtt) of the first probe sent to the gateway. If the probe has a timeout the rtt is set to -1.

applTracerouteProbe2RTT.name: applTracerouteProbe2RTT
applTracerouteProbe2RTT.description: This object contains the round trip time (rtt) of the second probe sent to the gateway. If the probe has a timeout the rtt is set to -1.

applTracerouteProbe3RTT.name: applTracerouteProbe3RTT
applTracerouteProbe3RTT.description: This object contains the round trip time (rtt) of the third probe sent to the gateway. If the probe has a timeout the rtt is set to -1.

diagTestTrapEnable.name: diagTestTrapEnable
diagTestTrapEnable.description: This object is used to disable or enable TestOver and TestStart trap for all tests. It is bit sum and possible bit positions are 1 TestStart trap 2 TestOver trap

diagApplTestStart.name: diagApplTestStart
diagApplTestStart.description: This trap signifies that an application test has been initiated.

diagApplTestStop.name: diagApplTestStop
diagApplTestStop.description: This trap signifies that an application test has completed. This trap compliments the diagApplTestStart trap.

diagIfTestStart.name: diagIfTestStart
diagIfTestStart.description: This trap signifies that a diagnostic test has been initiated.

diagIfTestOver.name: diagIfTestOver
diagIfTestOver.description: This trap signifies that a diagnostic test has completed. This trap compliments the diagIfTestStart trap
